To create a basic website, you'll need to understand HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Let's discuss the essentials of coding these components.

1. HTML (Hypertext Markup Language)
HTML is the structural foundation of a webpage, defining the content and its layout.

Example:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My Website</title>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <p>This is some example text on my page.</p>
    </main>
    <footer>
        <p>Copyright © 2022 - All rights reserved</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

The example above demonstrates the essential structure of an HTML page. From top to bottom, it contains the DOCTYPE declaration, the `<!DOCTYPE html>`, the `<html>` tag, the `<head>` section (where you can insert meta information), the `<body>` section (where you place content), and the structure of the page's different sections (`header`, `main`, and `footer`).

2. CSS (Cascading Style Sheets)
CSS is responsible for beautifying and styling your HTML elements.

Example:

```css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

header {
    text-align: center;
    background-color: #333;
    color: white;
    padding: 15px;
}

h1 {
    margin: 0;
}

main {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 20px;
}

footer {
    text-align: center;
    background-color: #eee;
    padding: 15px;
}
```

This example targets specific sections or elements of the page and applies styling to them.

